Chaney King Fun Ride
description: 3 Lap, 30 mile fun ride going counterclockwise around the Air Force Academy.  This ride will take place at the same time as the Front Range Falcon Classic.  The racers will be travelling clockwise around base. This ride is ideal for watching the racers tackle the hard climbs and screaming descents of the Air Force Academy.  The money raised from this event will support the Falcon Foundation.
course: The course begins at the cadet fields at the North West corner fo the Air Force Academy and travels counter clockwise around base.  The riders will descend pine drive, ride north on stadium blvd and turn left up North Gate Blvd.  After 3 laps riders will return back to the field area.
registration: Register at www.sportbaseonline.com and recieve a free shirt.
directions: I-25 north or south to Academy Blvd/US Air Force Academy South Gate exit.  Go west onto AF Academy.  Show drivers license at gate, continue on stadium blvd until end and make a left at North Gate/Academy Drive.  Follow signs to parking.
